  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nSometimes users need to quickly mark all notifications as read, so they can start from a pristine state. Currently they need to individually mark notifications as read, which is tedious, especially for users with lots of unread notifications.\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n\r\nGive users the option to mark all notifications as read. See in Figma for all the details https://www.figma.com/file/eDfxTa9IoaCMUy5cLTp0ys/Shell-for-Mobile?node-id=5305%3A519966&t=ANqnR83VEKQqzHRY-0\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46027/214678442-6f0fa9c6-df44-465d-a460-c8d0ee744534.png\" width=\"800\" />\r\n\r\n### Out of scope\r\n\r\n- Notification settings to customize if the user should see a confirmation dialog or not before marking all as read.\r\n- Undo the operation of marking all as read (this should be done in a separate issue).",
